is energy stored in the environment,}{\insrsid14239721  perhaps temporarily, and Q}{\sub\insrsid14239721 1 }{\insrsid14239721 is the dissipated heat.}{\insrsid13980363 
\par }{\insrsid14572347 \tab The energy symbol E represents the familiar thermodynamic state function, which usually consists of internal chemical energy of constitution, but may also include such forms as gravitational energy. Q and W are never state}{
\insrsid13591443  }{\insrsid14572347 functions but depend on the path of application.
\par }{\insrsid13591443 \tab A point of some significance here is that not only is there an unavoidable waste energy E}{\sub\insrsid13591443 1 }{\insrsid13591443 + Q}{\sub\insrsid13591443 1 }{\insrsid13591443 , depending on machine efficiency, }{
\insrsid5780765 but also the "useful work" W must inevitably be dissipated in its entirety as pollution E}{\sub\insrsid5780765 2 }{\insrsid5780765 + Q}{\sub\insrsid5780765 2 }{\insrsid5780765 , in what might be called the "Rumford Effect."}{
\insrsid2844712  Thus the environmental side effects of energy utilization extend far beyond energy production and industrial use to consumer use and "wear-out", in which the energy of constitution, in indeterminate but usually deleterious modes}{
